question:
Consider the following code. What is printed to the console?
```java
try {
    try {
        int[] arr = new int[5];
        arr[10] = 50; // Line A
    } catch (ArithmeticException e) {
        System.out.print("Inner Catch ");
    }
    System.out.print("After Inner Try ");
} catch (ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException e) {
    System.out.print("Outer Catch ");
}
```

What is the output of the following code?
```java
try {
    try {
        throw new NullPointerException();
    } catch (NullPointerException e) {
        System.out.print("Caught NPE ");
        throw new ArithmeticException(); // Line B
    }
} catch (Exception e) {
    System.out.print("Caught General Exception");
}
```
